         <div>
            <head>Introduction</head>
            <p>This document compiles various concrete use cases implementing the suggested <gi>standOff</gi> element in order to refine the possible constraints that may bear upon it and its
               sub-elements. It is based on the experience gained in various projects since the initial workshop that launched the definition of this element as well as on some ongoing activities that
               are being pursued in several national projects in France and Germany (mong others), in internaitonal institutions (EPO) as well as in the content of several ISO projects (some of which
               have already been published as standards).</p>
            <p>The major conclusions that can be drawn from these use cases are the following:</p>
            <list>
               <item>...</item>
            </list>
